        <div class="boxbrdlouter">
          <div class="pnltextm">
            <p>
              <span class="pgloc">
                <a name="pg0043">[page&nbsp;43:]</a>
              </span>
            </p>
            <h1 class="pmttl" style="font-size: 120%; letter-spacing: .10em;">
              <b>TAMERLANE.</b>
            </h1>
            <p class="ornline"> &mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash; </p>
            <div class="quotepoem" style="max-width: 20em;">
              <p class="pmsec"> 1 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Kind solace in a dying hour! &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Such, father, is not (now) my theme &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> I will not madly deem that power </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> Of Earth may shrive me of the sin </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> Unearthly pride hath revell&apos;d in &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> I have no time to dote or dream: </p>
              <p class="pmline"> You call it hope &mdash; that fire of fire! </p>
              <p class="pmline"> It is but agony of desire: </p>
              <p class="pmline"> If I <i>can</i> hope &mdash; Oh God! I can &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Its fount is holier &mdash; more divine &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> I would not call thee fool, old man, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> But such is not a gift of thine. </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 2 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Know thou the secret of a spirit </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Bow&apos;d from its wild pride into shame. </p>
              <p class="pmline"> O! yearning heart! I did inherit </p>
              <p class="pmlinew" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Thy withering portion with the fame, <span class="pgloc"><a
                    name="pg0044">[page&nbsp;44:]</a></span>
              </p>
              <p class="pmline"> The searing glory which hath shone </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Amid the jewels of my throne, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Halo of Hell! and with a pain </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Not Hell shall make me fear again &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> O! craving heart, for the lost flowers </p>
              <p class="pmline"> And sunshine of my summer hours! </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Th&rsquo; undying voice of that dead time, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> With its interminable chime, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Rings, in the spirit of a spell, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Upon thy emptiness &mdash; a knell. </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 3 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> I have not always been as now: </p>
              <p class="pmline">
                <a name="28">The</a> fever&apos;d diadem on my brow </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> I claim&apos;d and won usurpingly &mdash;&mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Hath not the same fierce heirdom given </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Rome to the Caesar &mdash; this to me? </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> The heritage of a kingly mind, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> And a proud spirit which hath striven </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> Triumphantly with human kind. </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 4 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> On mountain soil I first drew life: </p>
              <p class="pmlinew" style="padding-left: 2em;"> The mists of the Taglay have shed <span class="pgloc"><a name="pg0045"
                    >[page&nbsp;45:]</a></span>
              </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Nightly their dews upon my head, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> And, I believe, the winged strife </p>
              <p class="pmline"> And tumult of the headlong air </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Hath nestl&apos;d in my very hair. </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 5 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> So late from Heaven &mdash; that dew &mdash; it fell </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> (&rsquo;Mid dreams of an unholy night) </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Upon me &mdash; with the touch of Hell, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> While the red flashing of the light </p>
              <p class="pmline"> From clouds that hung, like banners, o&apos;er, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Appeared to my half-closing eye </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> The pageantry of monarchy, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> And the deep trumpet-thunder&apos;s roar </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Came hurriedly upon me, telling </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> Of human battle, where my voice, </p>
              <p class="pmlinew" style="padding-left: 2em;"> My own voice, silly child! &mdash; was swelling </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> (O! how my spirit would rejoice, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> And leap within me at the cry) </p>
              <p class="pmline"> The battle-cry of Victory! </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 6 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> The rain came down upon my head </p>
              <p class="pmlinew" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Unshelter&apos;d &mdash; and the heavy wind <span class="pgloc"><a
                    name="pg0046">[page&nbsp;46:]</a></span>
              </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Was giantlike &mdash; so thou, my mind! &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> It was but man, I thought, who shed </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Laurels upon me: and the rush &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> The torrent of the chilly air </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Gurgled within my ear the crush </p>
              <p class="pmlinew" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Of empires &mdash; with the captive&apos;s prayer &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> The hum of suiters &mdash; and the tone </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Of flattery &rsquo;round a sovereign&apos;s throne. </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 7 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> My passions, from that hapless hour, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Usurp&apos;d a tyranny which men </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Have deem&apos;d, since I have reach&apos;d to power; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> My innate nature &mdash; be it so: </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> But, father, there liv&apos;d one who, then, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Then &mdash; in my boy-hood &mdash; when their fire </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> Burn&apos;d with a still intenser glow, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> (For passion must, with youth, expire) </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> E&rsquo;en <i>then</i> who knew this iron heart </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> In woman&apos;s weakness had a part. </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 8 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> I have no words &mdash; alas! &mdash; to tell </p>
              <p class="pmlinew"> The loveliness of loving well! <span class="pgloc"><a name="pg0047">[page&nbsp;47:]</a></span>
              </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Nor would I now attempt to trace </p>
              <p class="pmline"> The more than beauty of a face </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Whose lineaments, upon my mind, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Are &mdash;&mdash; shadows on th&rsquo; unstable wind: </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Thus I remember having dwelt </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Some page of early lore upon, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> With loitering eye, till I have felt </p>
              <p class="pmline"> The letters &mdash; with their meaning &mdash; melt </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> To fantasies &mdash; with none. </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 9 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> O! she was worthy of all love! </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Love &mdash; as in infancy was mine &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> &rsquo;Twas such as angel minds above </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Might envy; her young heart the shrine </p>
              <p class="pmline"> On which my ev&rsquo;ry hope and thought </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Were incense &mdash; then a goodly gift, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> </p>
              <p class="pmlinew" style="padding-left: 2em;"> For they were childish &mdash; and upright &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Pure &mdash;&mdash; as her young example taught: </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Why did I leave it, and, adrift, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Trust to the fire within, for light? </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 10 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> We grew in age &mdash; and love &mdash; together &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmlinew" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Roaming the forest, and the wild; <span class="pgloc"><a name="pg0048"
                    >[page&nbsp;48:]</a></span>
              </p>
              <p class="pmline"> My breast her shield in wintry weather &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> And, when the friendly sunshine smil&apos;d, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> And she would mark the opening skies, </p>
              <p class="pmline">
                <i>I</i> saw no Heaven &mdash; but in her eyes. </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 11 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline">
                <a name="102">&shy;</a> Young Love&apos;s first lesson is &mdash;&mdash; the heart: </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> For &apos;mid that sunshine, and those smiles, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> When, from our little cares apart, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> And laughing at her girlish wiles, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> I&apos;d throw me on her throbbing breast, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> And pour my spirit out in tears &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> There was no need to speak the rest &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> No need to quiet any fears </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Of her &mdash; who ask&apos;d no reason why, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> But turn&apos;d on me her quiet eye! </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 12 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Yet <i>more</i> than worthy of the love </p>
              <p class="pmline"> My spirit struggled with, and strove, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> When, on the mountain peak, alone, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Ambition lent it a new tone &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> I had no being &mdash; but in thee: </p>
              <p class="pmlinew" style="padding-left: 2em;"> The world, and all it did contain <span class="pgloc"><a name="pg0049"
                    >[page&nbsp;49:]</a></span>
              </p>
              <p class="pmline"> In the earth &mdash; the air &mdash; the sea &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Its joy &mdash; its little lot of pain </p>
              <p class="pmline"> That was new pleasure &mdash;&mdash; the ideal, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Dim, vanities of dreams by night &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> And dimmer nothings which were real &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> (Shadows &mdash; and a more shadowy light!) </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Parted upon their misty wings, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> And, so, confusedly, became </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> Thine image and &mdash; a name &mdash; a name! </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Two separate &mdash; yet most intimate things. </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 13 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> I was ambitious &mdash; have you known </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> The passion, father? You have not: </p>
              <p class="pmline"> A cottager, I mark&apos;d a throne </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Of half the world as all my own, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> And murmur&apos;d at such lowly lot &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> But, just like any other dream, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> Upon the vapor of the dew </p>
              <p class="pmline"> My own had past, did not the beam </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> Of Beauty which did while it thro&apos; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> The minute &mdash; the hour &mdash; the day &mdash; oppress </p>
              <p class="pmlinew"> My mind with double loveliness. <span class="pgloc"><a name="pg0050">[page&nbsp;50:]</a></span>
              </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 14 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> We walk&apos;d together on the crown </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Of a high mountain which look&apos;d down </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Afar from its proud natural towers </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Of rock and forest, on the hills &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> The dwindled hills! begirt with bowers </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> And shouting with a thousand rills. </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 15 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> I spoke to her of power and pride, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> But mystically &mdash; in such guise </p>
              <p class="pmline"> That she might deem it nought beside </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> The moment&apos;s converse; in her eyes </p>
              <p class="pmline"> I read, perhaps too carelessly &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> A mingled feeling with my own &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> The flush on her bright cheek, to me </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Seem&apos;d to become a queenly throne </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Too well that I should let it be </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Light in the wilderness alone. </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 16 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> I wrapp&apos;d myself in grandeur then, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> And donn&apos;d a visionary crown &mdash;&mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> Yet it was not that Fantasy </p>
              <p class="pmlinew" style="padding-left: 4em;"> Had thrown her mantle over me &mdash; <span class="pgloc"><a
                    name="pg0051">[page&nbsp;51:]</a></span>
              </p>
              <p class="pmline"> But that, among the rabble &mdash; men, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> Lion ambition is chain&apos;d down &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> And crouches to a keeper&apos;s hand &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Not so in deserts where the grand </p>
              <p class="pmline"> The wild &mdash; the terrible conspire </p>
              <p class="pmline"> With their own breath to fan his fire. </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 17 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Look &rsquo;round thee now on Samarcand! &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Is she not queen of Earth? her pride </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Above all cities? in her hand </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Their destinies? in all beside </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Of glory which the world hath known </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Stands she not nobly and alone? </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Falling &mdash; her veriest stepping-stone </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Shall form the pedestal of a throne &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> And who her sovereign? Timour &mdash; he </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Whom the astonished people saw </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Striding o&apos;er empires haughtily </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> A diadem&apos;d outlaw &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 18 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> O! human love! thou spirit given, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> On Earth, of all we hope in Heaven! </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Which fall&apos;st into the soul like rain </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Upon the Siroc wither&apos;d plain, <span class="pgloc"><a name="pg0052">[page&nbsp;52:]</a></span>
              </p>
              <p class="pmline"> And failing in thy power to bless </p>
              <p class="pmline"> But leav&apos;st the heart a wilderness! </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Idea! which bindest life around </p>
              <p class="pmline"> With music of so strange a sound </p>
              <p class="pmline"> And beauty of so wild a birth &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Farewell! for I have won the Earth! </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 19 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> When Hope, the eagle that tower&apos;d, could see </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> No cliff beyond him in the sky, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> His pinions were bent droopingly &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> And homeward turn&apos;d his soften&apos;d eye. </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 20 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> &rsquo;Twas sunset: when the sun will part </p>
              <p class="pmline"> There comes a sullenness of heart </p>
              <p class="pmline"> To him who still would look upon </p>
              <p class="pmline"> The glory of the summer sun. </p>
              <p class="pmline"> That soul will hate the ev&rsquo;ning mist </p>
              <p class="pmline"> So often lovely, and will list </p>
              <p class="pmline"> To the sound of the coming darkness (known </p>
              <p class="pmline"> To those whose spirits harken) as one </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Who, in a dream of night, <i>would</i> fly </p>
              <p class="pmlinew"> But <i>cannot</i> from a danger nigh. <span class="pgloc"><a name="pg0053"
                  >[page&nbsp;53:]</a></span>
              </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 21 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> What tho&apos; the moon &mdash; the white moon </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Shed all the splendor of her noon, </p>
              <p class="pmline">
                <i>Her</i> smile is chilly &mdash; and <i>her</i> beam, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> In that time of dreariness, will seem </p>
              <p class="pmline"> [So like you gather in your breath] </p>
              <p class="pmline"> A portrait taken after death. </p>
              <p class="pmline"> And boyhood is a summer sun </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Whose waning is the dreariest one &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> For all we live to know is known </p>
              <p class="pmline"> And all we seek to keep hath flown &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Let life, then, as the day-flower, fall </p>
              <p class="pmline"> With the noon-day beauty &mdash; which is all. </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 22 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> I reach&apos;d my home &mdash; my home no more &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> For all had flown who made it so &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> I pass&apos;d from out its mossy door, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> And, tho&apos; my tread was soft and low, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> A voice came from the threshold stone </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Of one whom I had earlier known &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> O! I defy thee, Hell, to show </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> On beds of fire that burn below, </p>
              <p class="pmlinew" style="padding-left: 2em;"> A humbler heart &mdash; a deeper wo &mdash; <span class="pgloc"><a
                    name="pg0054">[page&nbsp;54:]</a></span>
              </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmsec"> 23 </p>
              <p class="pmbreak"> &thinsp; </p>
              <p class="pmline">
                <a name="222">&shy;</a> Father, I firmly do believe &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> I <i>know</i> &mdash; for Death who comes for me </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> From regions of the blest afar, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Where there is nothing to deceive, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 4em;"> Hath left his iron gate ajar, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> And rays of truth you cannot see </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Are flashing thro&apos; Eternity &mdash;&mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> I do believe that Eblis hath </p>
              <p class="pmline"> A snare in ev&rsquo;ry human path &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Else how, when in the holy grove </p>
              <p class="pmline"> I wandered of the idol, Love, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Who daily scents his snowy wings </p>
              <p class="pmline"> With incense of burnt offerings </p>
              <p class="pmline"> From the most unpolluted things, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Whose pleasant bowers are yet so riven </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Above with trelliced rays from Heaven </p>
              <p class="pmline"> No mote may shun &mdash; no tiniest fly </p>
              <p class="pmline"> The light&rsquo;ning of his eagle eye &mdash; </p>
              <p class="pmline"> How was it that Ambition crept, </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> Unseen, amid the revels there, </p>
              <p class="pmline"> Till growing bold, he laughed and leapt </p>
              <p class="pmline" style="padding-left: 2em;"> In the tangles of Love&apos;s very hair? </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bottom">
              <p> &thinsp; </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="boxbrdlouter">
          <p class="seprline"> &infin;&infin;&infin;&infin;&infin;&infin;&infin; </p>
        </div>
        <br />
